<p class="p">Changes in temperature provoked by changes in CO
 <sub class="sub">2</sub> concentration are given by 
 <disp-formula id="pone.0184480.e004" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0184480.e004.jpg" id="pone.0184480.e004g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M4" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mo class="mo">Δ</mo>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">T</mi>
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mfrac class="mfrac">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">σ</mi>
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">c</mi>
        <mi class="mi">i</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">c</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mtext class="mtext">pre</mtext>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
     <mo class="mo">−</mo>
     <mfrac class="mfrac">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">T</mi>
        <mi class="mi">i</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mi class="mi">τ</mi>
     </mfrac>
     <mo class="mo">,</mo>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label class="label">(4)</label>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic class="italic">σ</italic> indexes the climate sensitivity, the effect doubling CO
 <sub class="sub">2</sub> concentration over pre-industrial levels, 
 <italic class="italic">c</italic>
 <sub class="sub">pre</sub>, would have on global mean temperature. The parameter 
 <italic class="italic">τ</italic> reflects natural time delays associated with changes in global mean temperature.
</p>
